data.content:
Three EF Core 10 breaking changes hit your code:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes a regular lambda, not an expression tree

Your entire expression-tree construction can be replaced with a simple lambda:

```csharp
// EF Core 10
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

The `Expression.Lambda` / `Expression.Call` machinery is no longer needed (or accepted).

---

### 2. Complex type column names — two changes

**a) Duplicate property names across complex types are now uniquified** by appending a number. Your `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` will generate a migration renaming one column.

**b) Nested complex types use the full path.** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` maps to `Payment_BillingAddress_City` (was `BillingAddress_City`).

**Fix:** Pin the old column names explicitly so no migration is generated:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, ab =>
    {
        ab.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street");
    });
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, ab =>
    {
        ab.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street");
    });
});

// For nested complex types:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment, pb =>
    {
        pb.ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress, ab =>
        {
            ab.Property(a => a.City).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
        });
    });
});
```

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gained a `string logCommandText` parameter (redacted SQL for safe logging):

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ← new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (constants may be redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for actual SQL
    }
}
```

Add the parameter to **all** implemented methods (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) — they all received the same addition.
